name: N-boc-3-(2-thienyl)-L-alanine

The thienyl group introduces additional pi-stacking interactions, estimated at around +10 degrees Celsius. The methoxy group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at around +5 degrees Celsius. The carbamate group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, estimated at around +5 degrees Celsius. The effects are additive.
